mparable to that of a $p$-polarized driver ($\theta^i=\epsilon^i=0$). Although in principle, a normally incident circularly polarized laser can also generate a circularly polarized attosecond burst\cite{pop18.083104Ji11}. However, the requirements on the driving laser pulse is  demanding and the XUV conversion efficiency is much lower than the corresponding oblique incidence case.

